Introducing new attributes in the raw data frame¶

In [52]:
# Identifying the time interval between the delivery start, pickup arrived, left pickup and dropoff fields respectively and adding to the dataframe

df_data['start_to_pickup_interval']=df_data['when_the_Jumpman_arrived_at_pickup']-df_data['when_the_delivery_started']
df_data['pickup_to_left_interval']=df_data['when_the_Jumpman_left_pickup']-df_data['when_the_Jumpman_arrived_at_pickup']
df_data['left_to_dropoff_interval']=df_data['when_the_Jumpman_arrived_at_dropoff']-df_data['when_the_Jumpman_left_pickup']

In [53]:
# Creating attributes to store the interval of delivery start, pickup arrived, left pickup and dropoff fields respectively in  minutes

def get_total_sec(row):
    return row.total_seconds()

start_p = df_data.start_to_pickup_interval.apply(get_total_sec)
t_pick = df_data.pickup_to_left_interval.apply(get_total_sec)
t_drop = df_data.left_to_dropoff_interval.apply(get_total_sec)

df_data['start_to_pickup_interval_min'] = round(start_p/60,2)
df_data['pickup_to_left_interval_min'] = round(t_pick/60,2)
df_data['left_to_dropoff_interval_min'] = round(t_drop/60,2)
In [54]:
# Identifying the disance in km between pickup and dropoff points for each delivery record in the dataframe

km_dist=[]

for i in df_data.index:
    km_dist.append(geopy.distance.vincenty((df_data['pickup_lat'][i], df_data['pickup_lon'][i]),(df_data['dropoff_lat'][i], df_data['dropoff_lon'][i])).km)
    
df_data['pickup_drop_distance']=km_dist

df_data.head()

Visual depicting Hours of Day with the most demand¶

The spikes in the graph also provides an idea that demand is usually high around the Lunch and Dinner hours of the day.

Analyzing time to place an order with Jumpman23¶

# Adding attribute to store the time taken to order in minutes

def get_min(row):
    return row.minute*60.0 + row.second
minute = df_data.how_long_it_took_to_order.apply(get_min)
df_data['min_to_order'] = round(minute/60,2)
